  "prompt": "I am planning my honeymoon in January 2017. Planning to visit Krabi, Phuket, Bangkok with veg food. How do I go about planning this?",
  "response": "Here's a step-by-step guide to planning your honeymoon in Thailand:\n\nItinerary Planning:\n1. Suggested Duration: 7-10 days\n- 3-4 days in Krabi\n- 2-3 days in Phuket\n- 2-3 days in Bangkok\n\nTransportation:\n- Fly into Bangkok (Suvarnabhumi Airport)\n- Take domestic flights/buses between destinations\n- Consider flights from Bangkok to Krabi/Phuket\n\nVegetarian Food Options:\nBangkok:\n- May Kaidee vegetarian restaurant\n- Broccoli Revolution\n- Vegetarian restaurants in Chinatown\n\nKrabi:\n- Vegetarian restaurants in Ao Nang area\n- Many restaurants offer vegetarian Thai dishes\n- Try Thai curries, Pad Thai without meat\n\nPhuket:\n- Blue Mango Restaurant\n- Vegan/vegetarian cafes in Patong and Phuket Town\n\nAccommodation Tips:\n- Book beach resorts in Krabi/Phuket\n- Consider romantic, couple-friendly hotels\n- Check reviews on TripAdvisor\n\nMust-Do Activities:\n- Island hopping in Krabi\n- Phi Phi Islands tour\n- Thai cooking classes\n- Bangkok temples and markets\n- Phuket Old Town\n\nRecommended Booking Platforms:\n- Booking.com\n- Agoda\n- Airbnb\n\nTravel Tips:\n- Check visa requirements\n- Get travel insurance\n- Carry cash and cards\n- Book in advance during peak season",
